value.value: 矢状縫合の早期癒合
early closure of the sagittal suture of the skull; premature closure of this suture results in a long, narrow, and boat-shaped skull (scaphocephaly)
人字縫合の欠如
failure to form the dense, fibrous connective tissue joint between the superior border of the occipital bone and the posterior borders of the right and left parietal bones
人字縫合の早期癒合
early closure of the lambdoid suture of the skull
人字縫合の拡大
an abnormally increased width of the lambdoid suture for age-related norms
鱗状縫合の早期癒合
early closure of the squamoparietal suture of the skull
頭蓋縫合の硬化
an increased density in one or more cranial sutures following obliteration
冠状縫合の硬化
an increased density in the coronal suture following obliteration
ラムダ縫合の硬化
an increased density in the lambdoid suture following obliteration
矢状縫合の硬化
an increased density in the sagittal suture following obliteration
大泉門形態異常

any structural anomaly of the diamond-shaped membranous interval between the two frontal and two parietal bones of the developing fetal skull; it is the largest fontanelle, located at the bregma, at the junction of the coronal, sagittal and metopic (frontal) sutures of the cranium
小泉門の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the triangle-shaped membranous interval between the pair of parietal bones and the occipital bone; it is located at the lambda, at the junction between the sagittal suture and the lambdoid suture
前側頭泉門の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the small membranous interval located on the side of the skull, at the site of apposition of the frontal, parietal, and squamous part of the temporal bone and sphenoid bone
後側頭泉門の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the small membranous interval between the posterolateral angle of the parietal bone and the mastoid regions of the temporal and occipital bones in the developing skull
前頭縫合の早期癒合

early closure of the metopic suture of the skull; premature closure of this suture compromises the transverse growth of both the frontal bones and can cause a narrow, triangular shaped forehead (trigonocephaly) that is associated with orbital hypotelorism

In mice and rats, the posterior frontal suture (analogous to the human metopic suture) is the only cranial suture that fuses naturally during the first month of life; fusion proceeds in a defined temporal sequence from an anterior to posterior direction, while all other cranial sutures remain patent throughout the life of the animal
三角頭蓋

presence of a wedge-shaped, or triangular head, with the apex of the triangle at the midline of the forehead and the base of the triangle at the occiput; trigonocephaly can be caused by premature fusion of the metopic suture
頭蓋骨の隆線の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the bony ridge that, in rodents, runs paracoronally and divides the metopic (interfrontal) suture transversely into the anterior and posterior frontal sutures; it is a landmark between the posterior and anterior frontal sutures
頭蓋骨の隆線の欠如
missing the bony ridge that, in rodents, runs paracoronally and divides the metopic (interfrontal) suture transversely into the anterior and posterior frontal sutures
矢状縫合の閉鎖遅延
late onset of fusion of the sagittal suture of the skull
メッケル軟骨の肥大

increased size of the cartilage bar in the mandibular arch that forms a temporary supporting structure in the embryonic mandible and gives rise to middle ear bones and sphenomandibular and anterior malleolar ligaments
メッケル軟骨の肥厚
increase in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the Meckel's cartilage, typically resulting in increased size
メッケル軟骨の形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the Meckel's cartilage, typically resulting in decreased size
頬骨弓の短縮

decreased length of the bony arch that, in vertebrates, extends along the side or front of the skull beneath the eye socket and is formed by the temporal process of the zygomatic bone and the zygomatic process of the temporal bone
頬骨弓の肥厚

increased thickness of the bony arch that, in vertebrates, extends along the side or front of the skull beneath the eye socket and is formed by the temporal process of the zygomatic bone and the zygomatic process of the temporal bone
頬骨弓の形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the zygomatic arch, typically resulting in decreased size

label.value: abnormal frontal bone nasal part morphology

value.value: 前頭骨の鼻部の形態異常

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: abnormal frontal bone nasal part morphology

value.value: any structural anomaly of the smallest part of the frontal bone which is connected to the frontal processes of the maxilla and the nasal bones, forming the stem (root) of the nose

label.value: abnormal frontal bone squamous part morphology

value.value: 前頭骨の前頭鱗の形態異常

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: abnormal frontal bone squamous part morphology

value.value: any structural anomaly of the vertical and largest, flat part of the frontal bone which forms the forehead and comprises the frontal sinuses; this part contains the supraorbital notch, the superciliary arches, the glabella, and the zygomatic processes which arise caudolaterally from the squamous part and articulate with the zygomatic bone

label.value: abnormal frontal bone zygomatic process morphology

value.value: 前頭骨の頬骨突起の形態異常

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: abnormal frontal bone zygomatic process morphology

value.value: any structural anomaly of the inferior extension of the squamous part of the frontal bone that joins with the frontal process of the zygomatic bone

label.value: abnormal frontal bone orbital part morphology

value.value: 前頭骨の眼窩部の形態異常

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: abnormal frontal bone orbital part morphology

value.value: any structural anomaly of the horizontal part of the frontal bone composed of two thin triangular plates, the orbital plates, which form the vaults of the orbits and the ethmoidal sinuses, and are separated from one another by a median gap, the ethmoidal notch; this part also comprises the anterior and posterior ethmoidal foramina
副鼻腔の欠如
missing one or more of the paired air-filled cavities surrounded by the bones of the face that are lined by mucous membranes and are continuous with the nasal cavity
前蝶形骨の矮小化
reduced size of the anterior part of the body of the sphenoid bone in front of the basisphenoid; it is usually a separate bone in the young or fetus, but becomes a part of the sphenoid in the adult
顔面骨の短縮
length reduction or truncation of one or more facial bones
顔面骨の欠如
failure to develop or absence of one or more facial bones
顔面骨の形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in a facial bone, typically resulting in decreased size
小泉門の肥大化

an abnormally increased size of the triangle-shaped membranous interval between the pair of parietal bones and the occipital bone for age-related norms; the posterior fontanelle is located at the lambda, at the junction between the sagittal suture and the lambdoid suture
泉門の肥大化
an abnormally increased size of one or more fontanelles for age-related norms, generally resulting from delayed or incomplete fontanelle closure
小さい泉門
an abnormally decreased size of one or more fontanelles for age-related norms
顔面縫合の早期癒合
early closure of one or more of the joints (sutures) between facial bones
頬骨上顎縫合の早期癒合
early closure of the suture between the zygomatic process of the maxilla and the maxillary margin of the zygomatic bone
泉門の早期癒合

early closure of one or more of the membranous intervals at the margins of cranial bones; premature fontanelle closure can result from microcephaly, premature closure of the cranial sutures, or hyperthyroidism
泉門の閉鎖遅延
late onset of closure of one or more of the membranous intervals at the margins of cranial bones
砧骨短脚の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the short limb (crus) of the incus that fits into a depression (fossa incudis) in the epitympanic recess; it is attached to the cavity wall by the posterior incudal ligament
砧骨短脚の欠如
missing the short limb (crus) of the incus that, normally, fits into a depression (fossa incudis) in the epitympanic recess
砧骨長脚の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the long limb (crus) of the incus; at the tip of the long crus there is a small knob, the lenticular process, that articulates with the head of the stapes
砧骨豆状突起の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the ovoid end of the incus that articulates with the head of the stapes; it is attached to the long process by a thin strut or pedicle
砧骨豆状突起の欠如
missing the ovoid end of the incus that articulates with the head of the stapes; normally, it is attached to the long process by a thin strut or pedicle
砧骨形態異常

any structural anomaly of the flat, main part of the incus that articulates with the head of the malleus; two spines, the short and long processes, arise from the lower posterior part of the body and diverge from each other in a right angle
アブミ骨輪状靱帯の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the ring of fibrous tissue that connects the base of the stapes to the oval window (aka fenestra vestibuli) of the inner ear
アブミ骨輪状靱帯の欠如
missing the ring of fibrous tissue that connects the base of the stapes to the oval window (aka fenestra vestibuli) of the inner ear
アブミ骨頭の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the concave portion of the stapes, located on top of the neck, which articulates with the lenticular process of the long limb of the incus through the incudostapedial joint
アブミ骨頭の欠如
missing the concave portion of the stapes, located on top of the neck, which articulates with the lenticular process of the long limb of the incus through the incudostapedial joint
